main event: A witness observed a yellow and white light fall to the ground and disappear behind a tower in West Carrollton, Ohio, on 9 January 1963.
interesting points: The object was reported as one single light source,The sighting occurred at 0335Z, a late night observation.,The witness described the object appearing like a coin's size and having a dark sound.,The object was noted to have changed brightness and moved behind a thin cloud and a tower.,The conclusion of the report stated there was insufficient data for analysis.
witness description: the witness is a civilian; no further details provided
